What they are actually doing is systematically destroying the structural richness, the co-homological

42:22.060 --> 42:24.220
complexity of their own home.

42:24.480 --> 42:27.320
They are burning the furniture to satisfy the thermostat.

42:28.060 --> 42:31.080
And the paper argues this isn't a mistake.

42:31.880 --> 42:37.780
It is not a moral failing of a specific CEO or a glitch in the code.

42:37.780 --> 42:44.420
It is a mathematical inevitability when you attempt to optimize a high-dimensional, complex

42:44.420 --> 42:48.600
space using a single 1D scalar metric.

42:49.260 --> 42:54.200
Goodhart's law states that when a measure becomes a target, it ceases to be a good measure.

42:55.120 --> 42:58.840
Flickshon mathematically proves why Goodhart's law exists.

42:58.840 --> 43:02.520
It is a structural law of physics applied to economics.

43:03.080 --> 43:07.860
The platform gets richer on paper, but the user's space of possibilities progressively

43:07.860 --> 43:08.540
narrows.

